April 7, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROTECT DISABLED AND OLDER ADULTS FROM FINANCIAL
3 EXPLOITATION AND TO UPDATE THE SAVINGS BANK LAWS TO INCREASE
4 ALIGNMENT WITH THE COMMERCIAL BANKING LAWS.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6
7 PART I. ENHANCEMENTS TO ARTICLE 6A OF CHAPTER 108A, "PROTECTION
8 OF DISABLED AND OLDER ADULTS FROM FINANCIAL EXPLOITATION"
9 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 108A-112 reads as rewritten:
10 "§ 108A-112. Legislative intent and purpose.
11 (a) Determined to fight the growing problem of fraud and financial exploitation targeting
12 disabled adults and older adults in North Carolina, the General Assembly enacts this Article to
13 facilitate the collection of records needed to investigate and prosecute such these incidents.
14 (b) The General Assembly finds that older adults in this State are at a statistically higher
15 risk of being targeted for financial exploitation, regardless of diminished capacity or other
16 disability, because of their accumulation of substantial assets and wealth compared to younger
17 age groups.
18 (c) The General Assembly recognizes that financial institutions have duties imposed by
19 law and by contract to conduct customer-directed transactions in a timely manner and in
20 accordance with their customers' instructions.
21 (d) The General Assembly intends to provide financial institutions with the tools and
22 protections to take action based upon the reasonable belief that older adults or disabled adults
23 who have accounts with the financial institutions have been or are the subject of financial
24 exploitation and to provide financial institutions and their employees immunity from liability for
25 taking actions as authorized in this Article.
26 (e) The General Assembly intends to balance the rights of older adults and disabled adults
27 to direct and control their assets, funds, and investments and to exercise their constitutional rights
28 consistent with due process with the need to provide financial institutions the ability to place
29 narrow, 30-day limited restrictions on these rights in an effort to decrease older adults or disabled
30 adults' risk of loss due to abuse, neglect, or financial exploitation."
31 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 108A-113 reads as rewritten:
32 "§ 108A-113. Definitions.
33 As used in this Article, the following definitions apply:
*H754-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) Customer. – A person who that is a present or former holder of an account
2 with a financial institution.
3 (2) Disabled adult. – An individual 18 years of age or older or a lawfully
4 emancipated minor who is present in the State of North Carolina this State and
5 who is physically or mentally incapacitated as defined in G.S. 108A-101(d).
6 (3) Financial exploitation. – The illegal or improper use of a disabled adult's or
7 older adult's money, assets, property, or other financial resources for another's
8 profit or pecuniary advantage.advantage, or any act or omission by a person,
9 including through the use of power of attorney, guardianship, or
10 conservatorship, to do either of the following:
11 a. Obtain control over the older adult's or disabled adult's money, assets,
12 or property through deception, intimidation, or undue influence to
13 deprive him or her of the ownership, use, benefit, or possession of the
14 money, assets, or property.
15 b. Divert the older adult's or disabled adult's money, assets, or property
16 to deprive him or her of the ownership, use, benefit, or possession of
17 the money, assets, or property.
18 (4) Financial institution. – A banking corporation, trust company, savings and
19 loan association, credit union, or other entity principally engaged in lending
20 money or receiving or soliciting money on deposit.
21 (5) Financial record. – An original of, a copy of, or information derived from a
22 record held by a financial institution pertaining to a customer's relationship
23 with the financial institution and identified with or identifiable with the
24 customer.
25 (6) Investigating entity. – A law enforcement agency investigating alleged
26 financial exploitation of a disabled adult or an older adult, or a county
27 department of social services investigating alleged financial exploitation of a
28 disabled adult.
29 (7) Law enforcement agency. – Any duly accredited State or local government
30 agency possessing authority to enforce the criminal statutes of North Carolina.
31 (8) Older adult. – An individual 65 years of age or older.
32 (9) Promptly. – As soon as practicable, with reasonable allowance to be made for
33 the time required to retrieve older data or records that are not readily or
34 immediately retrievable due to their current storage media.
35 (10) Trusted contact. – Includes any of the following:
36 a. A natural person 18 years of age or older whom the customer has
37 expressly identified pursuant to G.S. 108A-114 in a financial
38 institution's records as the person who may be contacted (i) about
39 either the account or the account owner to address possible financial
40 exploitation or to confirm the specifics of the account owner's current
41 contact information or health status; (ii) to determine the identity of
42 any conservator, executor, trustee, or agent; or (iii) to address any
43 other concern reasonably related to the administration of the account.
44 b. A joint account owner, additional authorized signatory, beneficiary of
45 the customer's account, or an agent under a power of attorney.
46 c. An attorney, trustee, conservator, guardian, or other fiduciary whom a
47 court or government agency has selected to manage some or all of the
48 financial affairs of the older adult or disabled adult.
49 d. A parent, spouse, adult child, sibling, or other family member of an
50 older adult or disabled adult whom a financial institution believes is
51 closely associated with the older adult or disabled adult."
