1 (a) A State savings bank may establish one or more branches in this State, whether de
2 novo or by acquisition of existing branches of another depository institution, with the prior
3 written approval of the Commissioner. The Commissioner's approval may be given or withheld,
4 in the Commissioner's discretion after considering any comments received within 14 days of the
5 date of publication of the public notice under subsection (c) of this section.
6 (b) A State savings bank may establish branches in another state, whether de novo or by
7 acquisition of existing branches of another depository institution, in accordance with applicable
8 federal law and the laws of the other state, upon prior written approval of the Commissioner. The
9 Commissioner's approval may be given or withheld in the Commissioner's discretion after
10 considering any comments received within 14 days of the date of publication of the public notice
11 under subsection (c) of this section.
12 (c) A State savings bank seeking authority to establish a branch shall make application
13 to the Commissioner in a form acceptable to the Commissioner. Not more than 30 days before
