21 application to the Commissioner and that comments received by the
22 Commissioner within 14 days of the date of publication of the public notice
23 shall be considered. The public notice shall provide the current mailing
24 address of the Commissioner.
25 (d) A State savings bank may conduct any activities at a branch in another state
26 authorized under this section that are permissible for a State savings bank chartered by the other
27 state where the branch is located, except to the extent the activities are expressly prohibited by
28 the laws of this State or by any rule or order of the Commissioner applicable to the State savings
29 bank.
30 (e) Upon receipt of an application to establish a branch, the Commissioner shall conduct
31 an examination of the pertinent facts and information and may request additional information
32 that the Commissioner deems necessary to make a decision on the application. In deciding
33 whether to approve a branch application, the Commissioner shall take into account such factors
34 as the financial condition and history of the applicant; the adequacy of its capital; the applicant's
35 future earnings prospects; the character, competency, and experience of its management; the
36 probable impact of the branch on the condition of the applicant State savings bank and existing
37 depository institutions in the community to be served; and the convenience and needs of the
38 community the proposed branch is to serve."
