23 SECTION 2.(d) G.S. 54C-60 reads as rewritten:
24 "§ 54C-60. Confidential information.
25 (a) The following records or information of the Commission, the Commissioner of
26 Banks, or the agent of either shall be confidential and shall not be disclosed:
27 (1) Information obtained or compiled in preparation of or anticipation of, or
28 during an examination, audit, or investigation of any association;
29 (2) Information reflecting the specific collateral given by a named borrower, the
30 specific amount of stock owned by a named stockholder, any stockholder list
31 supplied to the Commissioner of Banks under G.S. 54C-22, or specific deposit
32 accounts held by a named member or customer;
33 (3) Information obtained, prepared, or compiled during or as a result of an
34 examination, audit, or investigation of any savings bank by an agency of the
35 United States, if the records would be confidential under federal law or
36 regulation;
37 (4) Information and reports submitted by savings banks to federal regulatory
38 agencies, if the records or information would be confidential under federal law
39 or regulation;
40 (5) Information and records regarding complaints from the public received by the
41 Division that concern savings banks when the complaint would or could result
42 in an investigation, except to the management of those savings banks; and
43 (6) Any other letters, reports, memoranda, recordings, charts or other documents
44 or records that would disclose any information of which disclosure is
45 prohibited in this subsection.
46 (b) A court of competent jurisdiction may order the disclosure of specific information.
47 (c) The information contained in an application is deemed to be public information.
48 Disclosure shall not extend to the financial statement of the incorporators nor to any further
49 information deemed by the Commissioner of Banks to be confidential.
50 (d) Nothing in this section shall prevent the exchange of information relating to savings
51 banks and the business thereof with the representatives of the agencies of this State, other states,
