11 "§ 54C-101. Directors.
12 (a) The corporate powers of a State savings bank shall be exercised by, or under the
13 authority of, its board of directors, and the business and affairs of the State savings bank shall be
14 managed by, or under the direction of, its board of directors.
15 (a1) The directors of a mutual savings bank shall be elected by the members at an annual
16 meeting, held under G.S. 54C-106, for any terms as the bylaws of the savings bank may provide.
17 Director's Directors' terms may be classified in the certificate of incorporation. Voting for
18 directors by deposit account holders shall be weighted according to the total amount of deposit
19 accounts held by the members, subject to any maximum number of votes per member which that
20 a savings bank may choose to prescribe in its bylaws. Voting rights for borrowers shall be fully
21 prescribed in a detailed manner in the bylaws of the savings bank.
22 (b) The directors of a stock savings bank shall be elected by the stockholders at an annual
23 meeting, held under G.S. 54C-106, for any terms as the bylaws of the savings bank may provide.
24 Director's Directors' terms may be classified in the certificate of incorporation.
25 (c) A director of a State savings bank shall have a significant ownership interest in the
26 State savings bank.
27 (d) A State savings bank shall have no less fewer than five directors. For good cause
28 shown, the Commissioner may approve boards of directors consisting of fewer than five
29 individuals to the extent consistent with other applicable law.
30 (e) The board of directors shall meet at least quarterly, an executive committee shall meet
31 in any month in which there is no meeting of the board of directors, and a loan committee shall
32 meet monthly.
33 (f) Except to the extent this Chapter or other applicable federal or State law imposes a
34 different standard, State savings bank directors have the duties, authority, and liabilities of
35 directors of corporations organized under Chapter 55 of the General Statutes.
36 (g) The board of directors of a State savings bank may appoint advisory directors to the
37 State savings bank's branches. No advisory director is liable for acts or omissions undertaken as
38 an advisory director under the laws applicable to the performance of the duties of a director of a
39 State savings bank, unless and only to the extent the advisory director undertakes or is delegated
40 authority as a director of the State savings bank."
41 SECTION 2.(f) G.S. 54C-102 reads as rewritten:
42 "§ 54C-102. Bylaws.
43 The bylaws and any amendments shall be certified by the appropriate corporate official and
44 submitted to the Commissioner of Banks for approval before they may become effective."
45 SECTION 2.(g) The Commissioner of Banks shall review Chapter 54C (Savings
46 Banks) of the General Statutes and form a drafting group, if appropriate, to prepare updates and
47 revisions to modernize the Chapter or to make recommendations on more fully integrating the
48 supervision of savings banks into Chapter 53C (Regulation of Banks) of the General Statutes.
49 The Commissioner of Banks shall prepare and submit a report on the findings and
50 recommendations to the Joint Legislative Commission on Governmental Operations within one
51 year of the effective date of this act.
